      <abstract>
        <p>Fulminant hepatic failure is a serious clinical syndrome with high mortality because of the limitation of therapeutic modality. However, survivors usually recover completely. Our experience with prostaglandin E1 (PGE1) treatment of a patient with acute fulminant viral hepatitis, who had a history of blood transfusion and immunosuppressive therapy for aplastic anemia, will be presented.</p>
      </abstract>
